    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "> 2 problems could arise using head state for validator indices:\r\n1.) if the chain reorg back prior to finalized_check_pt to SetA. Users and applications will not be able to get validatorSetB\r\n\r\nIs this actually a concern? Can validators join be assigned a validator index without finalization? \r\nWouldn't validatorSetA always be the same as validatorSetB in this case?\r\n\r\n> 2.) If the chain finalizes a conflict checkpoint with validatorSetC, the node will have trouble retrieving each set as it relies on the head state\r\n\r\nWhat is validator set C?",
